@node sect0 "Name"
samsnap - convert Sam snap or Messenger files to .SNA and vice versa 
@endnode

@node sect1 "Synopsis"
@{b}samsnap file1 [ file2 ]@{ub} 
@endnode

@node sect2 "Description"
If file1 is a Sam snap or .P file, then @{i}samsnap@{ui} converts it to .SNA format.  If file1 is a .SNA file, then @{i}samsnap@{ui} converts it to Sam snap format.  Sam snap format is the output obtained from using @{i}samread@{ui} to read a snapshot file from disk.  A .P file is a 65536-byte file produced by a device known as the Messenger. Note that @{i}samsnap@{ui} cannot create .P files (because a copy of the Messenger ROM would be required). The input file must have length 49174 (in which case it is assumed to be a Sam snap file), 65536 (in which case it is assumed to be a .P file) or 49179 (in which case it is assumed to be a .SNA file).  If file2 is named, then the output is written to this file, otherwise the output is written to the standard output. 


@endnode

@node sect3 "See Also"
samtools(1), samread(1), samwrite(1)  
@endnode
